This paper focuses on adversarial robustness of neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the sub-fields of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of adversarial attacks and defenses, which is a topic in computer security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper proposes a new training method for neural networks, which falls under the sub-field of neural networks (cs.NE).
